          <div id="content">
            
            <!--
<div id="box">
  <div class="big">
    <p>
      <strong>Wiseheart Design</strong> is an interface design company located near
      Raleigh, North Carolina, owned and operated by John W. Long.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
-->
<p>
  <img align="right" alt="John W. Long" height="160" src="/images/john.jpg" width="160" />
  <!-- <strong>About John</strong> &#8211; -->
  I am an interface designer with a zeal for virtue, simplicity, and beauty in all that I create.
  My background is in both programming and design. This allows me to optimize my work so that it is very easy to implement.
</p>
<p>
  I mostly work on <a href="http://rubyonrails.org">Ruby&nbsp;on&nbsp;Rails</a> projects.
</p>
<p>
  I can help break down your ideas into manageable, achievable goals and leverage them to their full potential.
</p>
<p>
  I strive for transparency on <em>all levels</em> of the design process
  and greatly enjoy working in the same room with my clients (though this is not essential).
</p>
<p>
  My expertise includes:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Rapid prototyping (paper, mockups, and HTML)</li>
  <li>HTML (all flavors)</li>
  <li>CSS (and <a href="http://wiseheartdesign.com/articles/2010/01/18/the-demise-of-css-why-sass-and-languages-like-it-will-triumph/">Sass</a>)</li>
  <li>Javscript (Prototype and JQuery)</li>
  <li>Ruby and Rails</li>
  <li>Design for iOS devices (iPhone and iPad)</li>
  <li>Test, Behavior, and Feature Driven Development</li>
</ul>
<p>
  I was an early adopter of both Ruby and Rails. My Ruby experience
  predates Rails itself by almost 2 years. I am somewhat famous for creating
  <a href="http://radiantcms.org">Radiant&nbsp;CMS</a> &#8211; the first viable
  open source Ruby on Rails content management system. I am an active
  contributor to open source with over <a href="http://github.com/jlong">twenty&nbsp;projects</a> on GitHub.
</p>
<p>
  <em><a href="http://workingwithrails.com">Working with Rails</a></em> lists
  me as being in the top 1% popularity out of over 16,000 Rails developers.
  (At the time of this writing, I was listed as #109.)
</p>
<p>
  I tend to work from home or at the nearest coffee shop.
</p>
<p>
  I enjoy talking with people about their projects. Contact me if you have something you want to discuss.
</p>
